{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01PCqUuvzrpDmXemNKfihPzn","type":"tool_result","content":"  1580→\n  1581→1. **Autonomous agents need hard stop conditions.** An orchestrator without a \"sprint complete\" exit condition will loop forever. This must be a pre-condition check, not something checked mid-loop.\n  1582→2. **State files need monotonic guards.** Story status should only move forward (backlog -> in-progress -> review -> done), never backward, unless explicitly commanded. A one-line `if (current === 'done') return` guard would have prevented all 52 occurrences.\n  1583→3. **In-memory state divergence is lethal in loop architectures.** Ralph reads state once, mutates in memory, writes back. Any external state change between read and write gets obliterated. Fix: re-read state from disk before every write, or use compare-and-swap.\n  1584→4. **Meta-work compounds.** Each no-op session generates a retro entry, an issues log entry, and a cost report update. The overhead of tracking the bug now exceeds the overhead of the bug itself.\n  1585→5. **\"Identified\" is not \"fixed.\"** The root cause was identified in session 17. It is now session 68. Identifying a bug without scheduling a fix is the same as ignoring it.\n  1586→\n  1587→### 7. Action Items\n  1588→\n  1589→| Priority | Action | Owner |\n  1590→|----------|--------|-------|\n  1591→| P0 | **Stop Ralph immediately.** Kill the loop. Sprint is done. | Human operator |\n  1592→| P0 | **Add sprint-complete exit condition** to Ralph's main loop: if all stories are `done`, exit cleanly. | Next sprint / story |\n  1593→| P1 | **Add monotonic status guard:** `if (currentStatus === 'done' && newStatus !== 'done') return` — prevent status reversion. | Next sprint / story |\n  1594→| P1 | **Re-read state from disk before write** in Ralph's loop to prevent stale-state overwrites. | Next sprint / story |\n  1595→| P2 | **Add `1-1-foo` phantom cleanup** — this test artifact keeps reappearing in cost reports. | Housekeeping |\n  1596→| P2 | **Cap no-op sessions** — if N consecutive sessions produce no story progress, halt automatically. Circuit breaker for the circuit breaker. | Next sprint / story |\n  1597→\n  1598→---\n  1599→\n  1600→*Session 68 retrospective generated 2026-03-28. Sprint is complete. Ralph must be stopped.*\n  1601→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_019iVgjSxXQk8MEApaygN8Fp","session_id":"1483394d-7ba5-4219-a1c5-699f99981ca9","uuid":"7b5027a2-6208-4d35-8503-90ba333a48d5","timestamp":"2026-03-28T06:18:14.892Z"}
